


           
      the semicolon  does anyone really understand the underlying purpose of a semicolon? in english class we all learn that it has some high valued purpose in the realm of english grammar.  our friends teach us the intricate uses of the semicolon in instant messenger (a winking face, a rose.)  but down inside the semicolon is just on a quest for a purpose, a core rationale that won't be easily taken away by such symbols as the tilda(~) or whatever this is(`).  isn't that what we all are on a quest for in life? the one thing that makes us different, unique, from the rest of the common world... anyone?
     

        
